flowRoot.flowPara: Figure Meta NW. Schematic of modified Needleman-Wunch algorithm for global alignment to a reference genome. Contigs (blue diagonals) are first locally aligned to a reference genome (A). All possible combinations of these local alignments are enumerated by realizing all paths connecting contigs from the upper left to lower right corner of the matrix (B). Each alignment is scored: matches contribute positive scores (dark blue lines in C), while indels (red) and mismatches (light blue) incur a penalty (D). The alignment with the highest score is selected as the best global alignment for the next step (E); ties among global alignments are resolved arbitrarily.
